cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dialog act classification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes and compares different methods for context representation learning in neural-based models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses recurrent neural network architectures and attention mechanisms for classification. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as dialog act classification can also be applied to spoken language. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper focuses on neural-based models for classification.
